Huynh Minh Phuoc is an Intern Network Engineer with 0 years of commercial experience, currently pursuing a Bachelor's in Computer Networks and Data Communications. Their core expertise encompasses CCNA-level knowledge in Routing & Switching, VLANs, OSPF, EIGRP, NAT, ACLs, IPv4/IPv6, PPP, GRE tunneling, DHCP, and EtherChannel. They have practical academic experience in deploying Distributed File Systems (DFS) with Active Directory, DFS Namespace, and DFS Replication on Windows Server, and developing Machine Learning-based DDoS Detection systems for Software-Defined Networking (SDN) environments using Classification Models. Furthermore, they have designed and configured intricate HQ–Branch network topologies, demonstrating proficiency in advanced routing protocols and network services.
Technically, Huynh Minh Phuoc is proficient in Python and PowerShell scripting, with hands-on experience in database management using MySQL and SQL Server. They are familiar with containerization via Docker and utilize network analysis tools like Wireshark, virtualization platforms such as Vmware and Mininet, and version control with Git/Github. Their practical skills extend to configuring and managing network security devices like Check Point R81 and Fortigate, administering Windows Server environments, and working with Ubuntu. Key domain knowledge includes Software-Defined Networking (SDN), Machine Learning applications in network security, and comprehensive understanding of Active Directory services.